Agartha represents part of Earth, and like Earth, Agartha has three levels of the planetary body. The Earth’s three primary body levels exist within dimensions 1, 2 and 3. There is a relationship of particle pulsation speed between Earth and her parallel dou- ble: The particle pulsation speed of Earth’s D-2 = anti-particle pulsation speed of parallel Earth D-1. Earth’s D-3 particle pulsation speed = that of parallel D-2, etc. The speed of particle pulsation within each dimensional band in the anti-particle universe is faster than that of the corresponding dimension in the particle universe. The particle pulsation speeds of the dimensional bands in the particle universe run one dimension behind those of the dimensional bands in the anti-particle universe.
